ABSTRACT
Implementations relate to an image grid with selectively
prominent images. In some implementations, a computer-
implemented method includes identifying a plurality of
images, where each image of the plurality of images has a
respective importance score. A subset of the images is
selected based at least in part on the respective importance
score for each image. The method determines respective one
or more cells in a grid for occupation by each of the images,
where at least one image of the subset is placed in the grid
such that it occupies at least two cells in the grid. The
method causes the images to be displayed in a user interface
on a display screen based on the grid.
